## 5. Promotion Engine Determinism (Phase 1)

### 5.1 Deterministic gates
- Promotable event types are enumerated (`PROMOTABLE_EVENT_TYPES`).
- Importance is deterministic (`IMPORTANCE_SCORES`).
- Event type normalization is deterministic (underscore ↔ dot, lowercase, trim).
- No LLM calls.

### 5.2 Deterministic outputs
For the same `(normalized event_type, redacted payload)`:
- promotion returns the same `PromotedEntry` or `None`.

### 5.3 Phase 2 statement
Phase 1 promotion is deterministic, but overall system determinism also depends on:
- timestamp stability/format,
- stable IDs,
- and filter semantics (see §6).

