## 8. Mirror Sync Correctness & Compatibility Findings

### 8.1 Blocking: Work-log SQL defect (as shown)
In the excerpt, the work-log sync query includes:

```

WHERE created_at_utc > ?
WHERE created_at_utc > ?

```

If present in the real file, this breaks sync (or makes it fail and be caught/hidden by error handling).

### 8.2 Blocking: Workspace/session UUID mismatch
- Runtime commonly uses `workspace_id="default"` as a directory and logical workspace key.
- Postgres mirror schema requires:
  - `workspace_id UUID NOT NULL`
  - inserts cast workspace/session IDs as UUID (`$2::uuid`, `$4::uuid`)

If workspace/session IDs are not true UUID strings, Postgres inserts will fail or be skipped.

### 8.3 Partial upsert semantics
Work-log mirror uses:

```

ON CONFLICT (id) DO UPDATE SET updated_at = EXCLUDED.updated_at

```

This updates only `updated_at`, leaving other columns potentially stale if the source entry changes.

### 8.4 Phase 2 statement
Mirror sync is not Phase-2-ready without:
- fixing the work-log SQL,
- aligning identifier types end-to-end (UUID vs text),
- defining an upsert policy that keeps mirror consistent.

