## 10. Risk Register (Ranked)

### P0 — Blocking correctness / data trust
- **Incorrect `more_count` after page 1** → breaks UX and “Top-3 boundary with pagination” promise.
- **Mirror sync SQL defect** → mirror may not populate at all.
- **ID type mismatch (UUID vs text)** → mirror writes skipped or failing silently.
- **Redaction not proven for promoted free text** → privacy/compliance hazard.

### P1 — Silent failure modes
- Cursor decode failure silently resets paging scope.
- No persistent checkpoint causes rescan on restart; relies on perfect idempotency.
- Approximate tag filtering may be mistaken as exact.

### P2 — Scale & quality
- LIKE queries degrade as corpus grows.
- Upsert updates only `updated_at`, leaving stale mirror content.

